58. He saw this opportunity as a turning point.\u003cbr /\u003e \u003cbr /\u003eRejecting the more experimental fiction of the 60s and 70s, he pioneered a precisionist realism reinventing the American short story during the eighties, heading the line of so-called 'dirty realists' or 'K-mart realists'. Set in trailer parks and shopping malls, they are stories of banal lives that turn on a seemingly insignificant detail. Carver writes with meticulous economy, suddenly bringing a life into focus in a similar way to the paintings of Edward Hopper. As well as being a master of the short story, he was an accomplished poet publishing several highly acclaimed volumes.\u003cbr /\u003e \u003cbr /\u003eAfter the 'line of demarcation' in Carver's life - 2 June 1977, the day he stopped drinking - his stories become increasingly more redemptive and expansive. Alcohol had eventually shattered his health, his work and his family - his first marriage effectively ending in 1978. He finally married his long-term parter Tess Gallagher (they met ten years earlier at a writers' conference in Dallas) in Reno, Nevada, less than two months before he eventually lost his fight with cancer.","isGrAuthor":false,"works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":298},"profileImageUrl":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1613953222i/7363._UY200_CR36,0,200,200_.jpg","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7363.Raymond_Carver","user":null,"viewerIsFollowing":null,"followers":{"__typename":"ContributorFollowersConnection","totalCount":4060}},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.jXrsNpdXiBiHqxq6V_Zxcg":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.jXrsNpdXiBiHqxq6V_Zxcg","__typename":"Book","legacyId":11437,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11437.Where_I_m_Calling_From","title":"Where I'm Calling From: New and Selected Stories","titleComplete":"Where I'm Calling From: New and Selected Stories","description":"By the time of his early death in 198